            "type": "single",
            "stem": "RT regimen: NCCN guideline: H&N V1.2019, GLOT-A 1of 2 -Ample data: 1.8Gy/frx/day significant lower local control rate vs 2Gy/frx/day 不應使用過小(1.8Gy/frx)的fraction size，避免使LC降低 若是腮腺深葉(deep lobe of parotid gland)的惡性腫瘤，且病理報告發現有顏面神經(CN VII)的神經周侵犯(perineural invasion)，則下列何者最不需要包含在術後照射(post-operative radiotherapy)範圍內？ 手術傷疤 (surgical scar)。 顳下窩 (infratemporal fossa)。 顱神經路徑(cranial nerve pathways)。 咽旁間隙 (parapharyngeal space)。 A (頭頸癌-唾液腺癌) 中等 Principles and Practice of Radiation Oncology, 2013 (6th edition), Perez and Brady’s, Chapter 43, p786 In case of a tumor of the deep lobe, the parapharyngeal space and the infratemporal fossa have to be covered adequately. In general it is not necessary to treat the scar to full skin dose because only 1% of the patient have a scar failure… In tumor with named perineural invasion,… it is important to cover the cranial nerve pathways from the parotid up to the base of skull. 在頭頸癌的治療中，下列何者接受合併放化療(concurrent chemoradiotherapy)比起單純放射治療(radiotherapy alone)能有最顯著的存活率改善？ 65歲女性，鼻咽癌cT1N0M0，接受治癒性合併放化療。 49歲女性，下咽癌術後pT2N3bM0，接受輔助性合併放化療。 75歲男性，聲門上癌cT3N2M0，接受治癒性合併放化療。 60歲男性，扁桃腺癌cT2N0M0, P16(-)，接受治癒性合併放化療。 B (頭頸癌-跨癌別) 低等 Principles and Practice of Radiation Oncology, 2013 (6th edition), Perez and Brady’s, Chapter 41, p749-750; Chapter 44, p806-807; Chapter 46, p844; Chapter 45, p825-826",
